    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix parameter naming inconsistency in NAS security key derivation functions\n\n### Summary\nThe NAS security mode control implementation contained a parameter naming inconsistency in the `_security_knas_int()` function declaration. The function was declared to take an `eea` (EPS Encryption Algorithm) parameter but was actually working with integrity algorithms. This caused confusion and potential misuse of the function.\n\nThe issue was introduced during a previous code review where function parameter names were not properly aligned with their actual usage. The bug manifested as incorrect parameter naming that could mislead developers about the function's intended behavior.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/EMM/SecurityModeControl.c`: Fixed parameter naming in `_security_knas_int()` and `_security_knas_enc()` function declarations to correctly reflect whether they work with encryption (`eea`) or integrity (`eia`) algorithms.\n\n"
}